# config/kubuntu_bloat.list
# List of packages commonly considered "bloatware" for Kubuntu installations.
# Each package name should be on a new line.
# Lines starting with '#' are comments and will be ignored by the script.
#
# WARNING: Removing system packages can have unintended consequences.
# Review this list carefully before running the debloater script.
# If you are unsure about a package, it's safer to leave it commented out or remove it from the list.

# --- Games (KDE specific games or general bloat) ---
kmahjongg
kmines
ksudoku
kpat
kblocks
kdegames-card-data
kdegames-arcade-data
kdegames-board-data
kdegames-puzzle-data
kdegames-strategy-data

# --- Internet and Communication (if not used) ---
akonadi-server # KDE PIM (Personal Information Management) backend
akonadi-backend-mysql # If not using MySQL for Akonadi
akonadi-backend-sqlite # If not using SQLite for Akonadi
plasma-browser-integration # If you don't use browser integration features
kdeconnect # If you don't use phone integration
konversation # IRC client
kmail # Email client
korganizer # Calendar and scheduling
kaddressbook # Address book

# --- Accessibility (only remove if you don't need any accessibility features) ---
# NOTE: Accessibility packages have been removed from this list as they can break
# important functionality for users who need them, and some applications may
# depend on them. Only advanced users should consider removing these manually.
# kmag - Screen magnifier
# kmouth - Speech synthesizer frontend
# kaccessible - KDE accessibility services

# --- Other ---
example-content # Example documents/pictures (less common in Kubuntu, but can exist)
